    "minides": "VinFast's debut Indian EV — assembled in Tamil Nadu, offering 59.6 kWh battery, Level 2 ADAS, 12.9-inch touchscreen, 7 airbags, coloured HUD, panoramic glass roof, and 463 km ARAI range at India's most aggressive midsize EV pricing.",
    "description": "The VinFast VF 6 launched in India on September 6, 2025, making it VinFast's first product in the Indian market. Assembled at VinFast's new plant in Thoothukudi, Tamil Nadu, it is offered in three variants — Earth, Wind, and Wind Infinity — all sharing the same 59.6 kWh battery pack in a front-wheel-drive layout. The Earth variant produces 174 PS and 250 Nm (468 km ARAI range), while Wind and Wind Infinity step up to 201 PS and 310 Nm (463 km range) for noticeably sharper performance. Key highlights include a 12.9-inch freestanding touchscreen (no conventional instrument cluster — a coloured HUD handles driver readouts), a fixed panoramic glass roof, 7 airbags, Level 2 ADAS with 360-degree camera, dual-zone automatic climate control with air ioniser, 8-way powered driver seat, ventilated front seats, 18-inch dual-tone alloys, and a 100 kW DC fast charger (10–70% in 25 minutes). VinFast offers 3 years of free charging at its V-Green network and a battery warranty. The VF 6 competes with the Hyundai Creta Electric, Tata Curvv EV, MG Windsor EV, and Mahindra BE 6."
  },
